From f0d311b41e1fa1ff60831b32e513ab9fe86bbd89 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Execution Bot <bot@execution.bot>
Date: Fri, 22 May 2026 07:02:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: sniper crash + migrations + full UX overhaul
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

CRASH FIX (was killing the whole deployment):
- sniper/service.ts: wrap handleLogNotification and handleAccountNotification
  in try/catch so an RPC timeout or rpc_all_failed error no longer crashes
  the entire Node process. Errors are logged and skipped instead.

MIGRATION FIX (was causing 'relation does not exist' errors):
- allInOneRenderFree.ts: default ENABLE_SNIPER_WORKER=true
- Build command in Render must be: npm ci && npm run build:render-free
  (this runs migrations automatically on every deploy)

UX improvements:
- All setting prompts now show clear descriptions with examples
- Status emojis on every dashboard field (🟢🟡🔴⏸️)
- STANDBY/PAUSED states show actionable guidance
- Positions: truncated mint addresses, clear TP/SL format, Live PnL button
- Orders: status emojis, Solscan links, truncated mints
- Notifications: SOL formatting, Solscan links, clean headers
